    "Britton teamed up with <a href=\"/pugina\">Augustus Welby Northmore Pugin</a> (illustrations) and E. J. Willson (documentation) to produce <em>Specimens of Gothic Architecture</em> 1821-1823, his most successful book and the lasting importance of his reputation.": [],
    "During the publication of his series, steel engraving supplanted copperplate which Britton had used.": [],
